main event: Unidentified flying objects were observed in the sky near Inwood, New York on August 15-16, 1961.
interesting points: The objects appeared to ascend, cross, and reappear in another location and direction.
The objects were observed for 5-10 minutes.
The observer was looking for a satellite when they spotted the objects, which appeared before and after the satellite passed.
The objects were described as being about the size of a baseball and lasting 5-10 seconds.
The objects appeared to change position as the observer started traveling south.
result: Insufficient Information to form a conclusion
